    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-06-04T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-06-04T08:00:00-05:00" n="79"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.512351 Double/335: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Straus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-04T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 4, 1936—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 4—9:08 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>456. Referring to the Embassy’s telegram 451, June 3, 4 p.m.,<note n="52"
                        xml:id="d79fn52">Not printed.</note> Foreign Office after further
                    consultation with the Treasury confirms that it is impossible for reasons of a
                    legal nature to extend the period for filing double tax convention declarations.
                    We, therefore, renew the suggestion made in our 450, June 3, 1 p.m.,<note n="52"
                        xml:id="d79fn53">Not printed.</note> that the Department may wish to make
                    this information available without delay to the interested firms. We are taking
                    steps to make this information available to American firms here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Straus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
